                <note rend="inline" type="source">875.00/136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-06T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1924—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 7—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Armistice declared evening 4th at the instance of the Government. Beys
                    fearful confiscation of estates. The same day the majority of the Government
                    deputies, a number of officials and families, fled to Durazzo. Tirana garrison
                    immediately took effective measures to insure public safety. Force of tribesmen
                    raised by Ahmed Zogu dissolving, carrying off arms. Nationalists insist upon
                    immediate exile of Ahmed Bey … Destroyer <hi rend="italic">Bulmer</hi> arrived
                    at Durazzo Wednesday afternoon. Copy to European Information Center.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
